data.description: Welcome to 2748 Pythagoras Circle, an expansive two-story home that seamlessly blends space, style, and functionality across its impressive 3,514 square feet. With 6 bedrooms and 4 bathrooms, this residence offers a harmonious balance between design and comfortable living. Upon entering, the first floor welcomes you with a seamless family room and dining room combo, creating an inviting atmosphere for gatherings. The well-appointed kitchen, adorned with granite countertops and stainless steel appliances, features an eat-in kitchen area and overlooks the spacious living room—a central hub for daily activities and entertainment. Adding to the allure of the first floor is a delightful screened-in patio, providing an extension of the living space and the perfect spot for al fresco dining or relaxation. The first floor also hosts a thoughtfully placed bedroom and bathroom, providing convenience and flexibility. This versatile space could serve as a guest room, home office, or a cozy retreat. Ascend to the second floor to discover a versatile loft area that can be used as a playroom, home office, or additional living space. The primary suite boasts ample space, a walk-in closet, and an ensuite bathroom with dual sinks, a garden tub, and a separate shower. Four additional bedrooms on the second floor provide plenty of room for family members or guests, each designed with comfort in mind. The second floor is enhanced by a screened-in balcony, offering a private outdoor space to enjoy the Florida breeze and picturesque views. Step into the backyard and you'll discover a lush tropical oasis that transcends the ordinary. This outdoor haven is adorned with a variety of exotic fruit trees, turning your private retreat into a vibrant and fruitful sanctuary. With a total of 3,514 square feet, this home is a haven for those seeking the perfect combination of elegance and practicality. This residence is equipped with solar panels that harness the power of the Florida sun, providing an environmentally friendly and cost-effective energy solution. Conveniently located in Ocoee, this residence provides easy access to local schools, shopping centers, and recreational amenities like the West Orange Trail. The proximity to major highways ensures a quick journey to downtown Orlando, and for those enchanted by the magic of Disney, the commute is a breeze, making family outings to the theme parks an effortless and enjoyable experience. Schedule your private tour today and envision the possibilities of living in this exceptional 3,514 square feet of well-designed living space with delightful outdoor retreat.
